"Moreover, responsibility-sharing within a team usually speeds up operational implementation. Typically, preliminary appraisal teams should possess skills in nutrition, public health, water and habitat, and in the sector of the economy that is affected by the crisis at hand. This may be agro-economy in the case of subsistence agriculture in Africa; in the case of former Yugoslavia, it would preferably require a sound understanding of general economics, and familiarity with urban and war-affected economies. \n# Triangulation\nThis concept is fundamental to organize data collection, in order to defi ne reality as accurately and quickly as possible. As such, triangulation reinforces the concept of optimal ignorance."